	<h1>Intro</h1>
	<p class="tagline">Trade journal companion for documenting, organizing, and analyzing your trading performance with markdown notes, screenshot galleries, and detailed statistics.</p>

	<h2 id="initial-configuration">Initial Configuration</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Three paths connect ThinkPad to your data.</p>

	<img src="/docs/prismchart/thinkpad/ThinkPad-20260126.jpg" alt="ThinkPad Settings - Files tab" />

	<p>If you used the installer, these paths are configured automatically. For manual installations, open Settings with the gear button and navigate to the Files tab to set them:</p>
	<ul>
		<li><strong>Notes Root Folder</strong> - Where your .md trade notes are stored</li>
		<li><strong>Screenshots Root Folder</strong> - Where your chart screenshots are saved</li>
		<li><strong>Trade Database File</strong> - Path to your MT5 export (trades.json)</li>
	</ul>

	<h2 id="timezone-setup">Timezone Setup</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Convert broker timestamps to your local time.</p>

	<img src="/docs/prismchart/thinkpad/ThinkPad-20260126-13.jpg" alt="ThinkPad Settings - Trade tab" />

	<p>Switch to the Trade tab in Settings. Set the UTC offset to match your timezone - Pacific Time uses -8, Eastern uses -5. This ensures all trade times display correctly when reviewing your history.</p>

	<h2 id="week-start">Week Start</h2>
	<p class="section-intro">Choose when your trading week begins.</p>

	<p>Select Monday or Sunday in the Trade tab. This affects how the calendar view groups and calculates weekly statistics.</p>
</DocsLayout>
